My history paper, which is ten pages long, is about the cold war.
My history paper, that is ten pages long, is about the cold war.
My history paper, is ten pages long, is about the cold war.
Doctor White, who received the award, is a heart surgeon. 
Doctor White, whom they gave the award to, is a heart surgeon.
Professor Dumbledoor, whose article we read, is giving a lecture on campus tomorrow. 


::Clause
A group of word that contains a verb and its subject. It is used as a sentence or as parts of speech

:: Phrase
A group of related words that is used as a single part of speech. It does not contain a verba and a subject.



Independent clause::
Expresses a complete thought and can stand bt itself as a sentence.

Subordinating clause(Dependent clasue)::
Does not express a complete a complete thought and cannot stand by itself.

I laughed, becuase she laughed.
I enjoy learning new things Since I love teaching.
I enjoy learning new things, and I love teaching.
I enjoy learning new things, so I love teaching.

There are six kinds of clause.



::Verb::
A verb is a word that expresses its subject's action or a state of being.
::Linking Verb:: 
A linking verb connects, or links

Relative clause
A dependent clause that starts with a relative pronoun 
who, that, which, whose, where

The boy who lived in Dhaka.
8th March 2019 Friday
Adjective Clause


Relative pronoun

