All adjective clauses are subordinative or dependent clause

This is sandwich. 
The sandwich is delicious. 
Mr. White made this.
This is sandwich that Mr. White made.
This is sandwich, which is delicious.

I drank a cup of tea, which was exotic.
The coffee that I like has been sold.
People whose library books are overdue must pay fine.
